post_text:
Update from Sno-Isle TECH:

Sno-Isle TECH is planning for a robust Fall opening. In order to do so, most of Sno-Isle TECH programs are employing nationally accredited online curriculum in alignment with industry standards for the program they teach. With a focus on equity for all students, Sno-Isle TECH will have materials to access at home if needed. Sno-Isle TECH is exploring offering in-person instruction as quickly and safely as possible, in small groups, per Snohomish County Health District guidelines. Sno-Isle TECH plays a vital part of high school graduation pathways for so many and Sno-Isle TECH is eager to stay on course with Sno-Isle TECH students. Please visit the Sno-Isle TECH Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/SnoIsleTECH/ and Webpage https://snoisletech.com/ for detailed information and updates.

post_text:
As of 4 p.m. today, March 3rd, there have been no students or staff members in Arlington Public Schools diagnosed with the Coronavirus. The district continues to follow the direction of the Snohomish Health District. The health department has not recommended that any Arlington schools close or that any Arlington students or staff stay home due to the Coronavirus.
Arlington Public Schools is taking the following steps to keep our students and staff safe from the Coronavirus:
• Buses will be sanitized daily
• Custodians are changing their daily cleaning routines to sanitize more surfaces in schools
• Teachers are encouraging students to wash hands and follow proper hygiene steps
